My husband and I have ordered from here in the past and we thought their pizza was good. However, this will be my absolute last time ordering from them. We ordered a large pizza and garlic knots. When we took a bite of the food, it tasted like it was reheated after sitting out all afternoon. The bread was dried out and the cheese had that cold pizza look. When I called to complain, the guy disagreed with me and tried to convince me that the pizza was fresh. I know the difference between fresh and old pizza. I asked if they could send us a new pie and he said, "No, we can't do nothing with that old pizza?! We can't sell that!" and I responded by saying, "Okay, we won't be ordering from you anymore" and he said okay. I'm highly disappointed in the way that handled this situation.Worst experience! What ever happened to the customer is always right!? Rather than charge this pie as a loss, he'd rather lose a customer for life. Never again!
